li.p:
Let t be time in minutes and H the temperature of the soda;

  \frac{dH}{dt} = 0.1(70 - H) = -0.1(H - 70)
.

Substitute T(t) = 75 + 30e^{-t/15} in for T in the differential equation
\frac{dT}{dt}= -\frac1{15}T+5 and verify the equality holds;
T(0) = 75 + 30e^0 = 75 + 30 = 105;
T(t) = 75 + 30e^{-t/15} \to 75 as t \to \infty.
